		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Thanks.<br /><br />Have you thought about having the shells just use the color of another enemy? Instead of leaving those three pixels of shading/highlighting on the edge, the sprites could use two separate palettes. For example, teal for the body and orange or lavender for the shell. This will maintain consistency in (lack of) shading while increasing the color count.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
