		<td><b>Re: Progress Thread - Nebs &amp; Debs Prequel</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Did some work on Deb's dash today. Currently,<br /><br />* Players can control the duration of dash at a gradient of 8 px as long as they are not colliding with anything.<br />* If a full dash can not be executed, a smaller dash (8 px) is attempted, and so on.<br />* Dashing does not reset the player's ability to jump (although I may change that later).<br />* The dash speed is 4 px a frame. At first I had it at 8 px, which feels pretty fun, but I the ability for more fine control is probably more important.<br /><br />Up next I need to animate debs for the dash and also I think add a target sprite so the player has a better idea of where they are dashing to. Right now it feels weird to dash through objects.<br /><br />Click the GIF preview to see the GIF animated correctly.

		
			<br clear="all" /><br />

